==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[ex-]]'' "out of", + ''[[spirare]]'', "to breathe" (from the idea that when a person dies, the breath of life goes out of them)

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪə(r)|-aɪə(r)]]

===Verb===
'''expire''', ('''expires''', '''expiring''', '''expired''')

====Intransitive====

# to [[die]]
#:''The old [[librarian]] '''expired''' last week.''
# to become [[invalid]]
#:''My [[library]] card '''expired''' last week.''
# to [[exhale]]; to [[breathe]] (out).

=====Translations=====
*German: [[versterben]] (1), [[ablaufen]] (2) [[erlöschen]] (2), [[verfallen]] (2), [[ausatmen]] (3)

====Transitive====
# to exhale something
#:''He escaped the garage and '''expired''' the carbon monoxide he had been breathing.''

=====Translations=====
*German: [[ausatmen]] (1)

